  "description": "The julenek (Christmas sheaf) is a Norwegian tradition of hanging oats or wheat for birds at Christmas. It tracks through three historical phases: pre-Christian harvest offering (associated with Freya and fertility), Christian reinterpretation as charity toward creation, and modern folk tradition.",
  "keywords": "syncretism, norway",
